The  National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI)  has warned bathers, surfers and paddlers to be cautious after a shark was spotted  at the main beach of Cape St Francis Bay. NSRI spokesperson Craig Lambinon said the shark was  swimming among surfers. Lambinon said the warning was also issued for those in the area of Tsitsikamma and Port Elizabeth. The shark is believed to be a great white. TimesLIVE